<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>CRIME STATISTICS</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Written evidence from the Police and Crime Commissioner for Gwent [CST0062]</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Thank you for your recent letters concerning crime statistics, particularly relating to</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Gwent Police.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Your Committee may wish to note that my wife and I booked a holiday in August 2013 and consequently I was out of the country from 18 November 2013 for five days.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Your kind invitation to attend your Committee hearing was received some two/three</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">weeks prior to my proposed attendance.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">I am sure that you will appreciate that there is a huge difference between "failing to turn up" (as reported in our local media) and actually being out of the country.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In response to your specific questions:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">1. The report that I jointly commissioned with the new Chief Constable was a snapshot of one week in July 2013.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The report deliberately concentrated on those incidents that were "questionable". I was not surprised that a high proportion, according to the counting rules, should have been recorded. This does not overly concern me as officers were acting in the interests of members of the public.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Finally the report gave me reassurance that behaviours that had been brought about by the previous obsession with reducing recorded crime had been addressed.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">2. I am content that the crime statistics in Gwent are recorded within the Home Office Counting Rules, and you will have heard our Chief Constable confirm to your Committee his commitment to ensuring an ethical approach to crime recording.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">3. I fully stand by my comments made in April 2013. Your Committee may wish to note that I have never used the term "manipulation" in relation to crime recording. It is my view that the imposition of daily ceilings on the number of crimes allowed to be recorded each day had a hugely negative impact on how officers dealt with victims of crime.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Gwent Police showed a reduction of 20% in recorded crime. The public did not believe the figures and neither did the officers.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Performance dials on computer screens and cheap and tacky banners "celebrating" success were viewed by many officers as unprofessional and totally misleading.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">It is important to note that during six months of "electioneering" and five months of attending mainly public meetings, the feedback was consistent- officers were more concerned about whether an incident should be recorded as a crime than actually providing a service to the victim.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">4. My Deputy attends the Data Quality Assurance Board which will be taking forward and monitoring an action plan resulting from the recommendations in the Crime Recording Report.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">The Chief Constable and I will continue to monitor crime recording practices by undertaking further reviews to ensure the public of Gwent can have confidence in the recorded crime levels.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">Additionally Gwent Police will be the subject of an inspection by HMIC in 2014.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">In conclusion I wish you and your Committee members best wishes for 2014.</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="font-size:12pt; line-height:115%; margin:0pt 0pt 10pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>